{
  "name": "Final Settlement",
  "story": true,
  "chapter": 6,
  "title": "Chapter VI — Final Settlement",
  "expedition": true,
  "theme": "dunes",
  "objective": "Breach the three desert rings west to east — raise all three relay pylons to wake the Settlement Anchor, then reach the great gate.",
  "time": 840,
  "captiveChars": [
    "atlas"
  ],
  "npcs": [
    {
      "id": "old-tarn",
      "name": "Old Tarn",
      "lines": [
        "You. Thought the swamp kept you. Then I thought the road did. Glad to be wrong twice.",
        "Take these — saved them since the crossing. The LYTH remembers everyone who ever carried it.",
        "Three rings of berms stand between us and the Anchor. A pylon sleeps behind each one. Light all three.",
        "The rings were raised to keep the Entropy out. Now it mans the windbreaks. Funny old frontier.",
        "Snipers and fire-kites nest along the sandbags — rush a gap and they can't lead you fast enough.",
        "Lurkers bury themselves in the open sand between the rings. They wait until you're close, then they aren't buried.",
        "Settle it for good, operator. I'm done walking."
      ],
      "gift": {
        "shards": 8
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "quiet-settler",
      "name": "The Quiet Settler",
      "lines": [
        "We held this frontier with a whisper, not a wall: keep the signal alive.",
        "Say it once and you are one of us. Keep the signal alive.",
        "Light all three pylons before you touch the gate — a quorum will not open for half a promise.",
        "The sand drags at your boots out there. So plan your dash through each ring; don't dawdle in the open.",
        "When the Anchor settles, finality spreads across the dunes. Out here we just call it morning."
      ]
    }
  ],
